<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-03-0869 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book traces the evolution of the Earth, mainly on the basis of radiogenicisotopes from half-life parent elements, and discusses it in terms ofthe latest developments in astrophysical theory, which impose uniqueconstraints on the origin and early evolution of the earth. Owing toits historical nature, this geohistorical study offers an approach toforecasting the future of the Earth yielding clues for the understandingof environmental problems, such as radioactive waste to disposal andclimate changes due to CO/sub 2/ increase.</TEXT></DOC>